{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"BytesRef"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The purpose of a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBytes"},{"type":"text","text":" is to keep the memory region that it holds"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"alive for as long as anyone holds a reference to the bytes.  When"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the last reference count is dropped, the memory is released. Multiple","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"unrelated callers can use byte data in the "},{"code":"GBytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" without coordinating","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"their activities, resting assured that the byte data will not change or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"move while they hold a reference.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"code":"GBytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" can come from many different origins that may have","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"different procedures for freeing the memory region.  Examples are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"memory from [func"},{"code":"GLib.malloc","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"], from memory slices, from a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MappedFile","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] or memory from other allocators."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"GBytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" work well as keys in [struct"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/d